        "unit": "kHz",
        "value": 30,
        "description": "20-50 kHz balances cleaning speed and heat accumulation in epoxy (melting point ~150-200°C); higher rates (>50 kHz) risk thermal buildup leading to matrix degradation. Source: Academic literature in Proceedings of SPIE (2021) on pulsed laser cleaning of polymer composites; trade-offs noted in manufacturer data from Coherent Inc."
