      "pulseWidth": {
        "min": 0.1,
        "max": 1000,
        "unit": "ns",
        "value": 20,
        "description": "Nanosecond regime preferred over ps/fs for cost-effective cleaning of polymers; 20 ns minimizes heat-affected zone (HAZ) in low-reflectivity epoxy (~5-10% at 1064 nm). Ps/fs (<1 ns) for ultra-precise but higher cost. Source: Laser physics research in Applied Surface Science (2019) on pulse duration effects in composite ablation."
      },
