        "value": 2000,
        "description": "Effective speeds ensure fluence delivery without excessive dwell time; 2000 mm/s optimal for light contamination on epoxy composites to prevent charring. Slower (500-1000 mm/s) for heavy contaminants. Source: Industry guidelines from Laserax equipment manuals; case studies in Journal of Cleaner Production (2020) for surface prep on composites."
      },
